        "id": "lQ2o6zgBosM_7mP4",
        "title": "Text 1",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Temperatures sometimes rise or fall suddenly. For example, </p><p>Montana holds the United States record for the fastest <em>rise </em>in temperature over a 24-hour period. In 23 hours, the temperature changed from –54˚F to 49˚F in the town of Loma.</p><p><strong>January 14, 1972 at 9 am: –54˚F   →   January 15, 1972 at 8 am: 49˚F</strong></p><p>Montana also holds the world record for the fastest <em>fall</em>. Browning, MT, saw temperatures drop from 44°F to –56°F, in less than 24 hours.</p><p><strong>January 23, 1916 at 9 am: 44˚F  →   January 24, 1916 at 8 am: –56˚F</strong></p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "2L8U7th3UCf7eAl_",
        "title": "Text 2",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>How many degrees Fahrenheit did the temperature rise in Loma, Montana? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "mjwo7XDG6YNxvf9Y",
        "title": "Text 5",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>103˚</p><p>-54°F increasing to 49°F </p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "vUKGoUVG8bGeQvfX",
        "title": "Text 3",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>How many degrees Fahrenheit did the temperature fall in Browning, Montana? </li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "vG2EDFRY0FZR1v0O",
        "title": "Text 6",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>The temperature fell 100 degrees. We can represent this as −100°F.</p><p>44°F falling to −56°F</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "QAiw8EEA_z_RB-Yp",
        "title": "Text 4",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<ul><li>How could you represent each change on a number line? With an equation?</li></ul>"
          ]
        }
      },
      {
        "id": "BnD_5JhnGuqo6vLD",
        "title": "Text 7",
        "display": "teacher",
        "content": {
          "type": "Text",
          "format": "html",
          "text": [
            "<p>Loma, Montana record: -54 + n = 49, with n = 103</p>"
          ]
        }
      },
